********************************************************************************
************************ NEXT COMMIT DESCRIPTION *******************************
********************************************************************************

The most important development was the implementation of the
pre-sorting stage (pre_sort()) which lefts stack A with three
sorted elements and stack B with the pre-sorted (statistically
speaking) remaining elements.

Debugging messages improved.

current_avg_pos_when_sorted member added to t_ps_stacks struct type.
the functions of dlclst_element_utils that receiver a dlclst* as an
argument were modified to receive a t_element as void* instead.

The ps_lang/print.c file was renamed to print_stacks.c to follow my
standards.

The functions in ps_lang_peek.c where updated according the int* type
list content to the t_type* type.

Most of the dlclst_element_utils functions where modified to take as
an argument the void* content instead of its related t_dlclst* node.

Documentation was improved and updated.

